HEADWORD: Butyrin
<hw>Bu"ty*rin</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A butyrate of glycerin; a fat contained in small
quantity in milk, which helps to give to butter its peculiar
flavor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

